Description: Blue glazed composition amulet, pierced lengthwise, in the form of an openwork double-sided wedjat-eye within an oval serrated frame.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 2 or 3
Curator's comments: The " symbolic eye" of "glazed ware", mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 74 § 72, " eye plaque", p. 111, pl. xli, 71. See London, BM, EA 18515 and 18518, similar.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 74 § 72, p. 111, pl. xli, 71)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.40, p.45, p.59, p.179, pl.21)
